Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
readTSVConfig(25.10)                                      readTSVConfig(25.10)

Name
       readTSVConfig  - Imports 3D IC configuration files of the whole design,
       including the stack die configuration  file,  power  net  configuration
       file and top-level netlist

Syntax
       readTSVConfig

       {[-stackedDieFile <filename>] [-powerFile <filename>]}

       [-chipName <chipName>]

       [-topNetlist]

       Imports  3D  IC  configuration files of the whole design, including the
       stack die configuration file, power net  configuration  file  and  top-
       level netlist.

Parameters
       <-stackedDieFile><filename>
              Reads the stack die configuration file.

       -powerFile <filename>
              Imports the power net configuration file.

       -chipName <chipName>
              Specifies the hierarchical instance name (chip) name of the cur-
              rent design in the top-level netlist.

              For example, if the current design is ramextra and the top-level
              netlist  is  below  it,  then  you  can  specify  the chip name,
              i_ramextra, as follows:

                              module top (...) ;

                     asic_entity i_asic_entity (.pin1(), .pin2(), ...);

                     ramextra i_ramextra (.pin1(), .pin2(), ...);

                     end module

       -topNetlist
              Imports the top-level netlist to support  3D  IC  design  in  OA
              mode.

              Note: You can import the top-level netlist in the non-OA mode in
              case  the  top-level netlist is not loaded during the design im-
              port.

Examples
              * The following command reads the stacked die configuration file
                and power configuration file and specifies  that  the  current
                design is named i_ramextra:

                readTSVConfig   -stackedDieFile   stacked_die.xml   -powerFile
                power.side -chipName i_ramextra

              * Below is the example of a stack die configuration file:

                <StackChip>

                  <TopDesign name="top" />

                  <Tier number=1>

                    <Chip name="i_asic_entity"  orientation="R0"  faceUp="Yes"
                llx=0 lly=0 sizeX=6000.0 sizeY=6000.0 scaleFactor=1 />

                  </Tier>

                  <Tier number=2>

                    <Chip   name="i_ramextra"   orientation="R0"  faceUp="Yes"
                llx=1500.0 lly=1250.0 sizeX=3500.0 sizeY=3000.0  scaleFactor=1
                />

                  </Tier>

                </StackChip>

              * Below is the example of a power net configuration file:

        VDD i_asic_entity   sharable

        VDD i_ramextra      backside

        VSS i_asic_entity   sharable

        VSS i_ramextra      backside

        Alias:

        i_asic_entity/VDD i_ramextra/VDD

        i_asic_entity/VSS i_ramextra/VSS

Related Information
